there's now more users for Anaconda's products

00:11:21.800 --> 00:11:24.720
as a result of this investment that's been made in iOS and Android

00:11:24.770 --> 00:11:26.180
to make it possible at all.

00:11:27.020 --> 00:11:28.580
It is very much a long-term project.

00:11:28.740 --> 00:11:30.740
But like this is iOS and Android stuff.

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:34.160
Conda as a project does not have particularly good support

00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:35.080
for iOS and Android.

00:11:35.620 --> 00:11:38.280
Eventually, hopefully not that far off, it will.

00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:42.480
But you don't get to Conda supporting it until Python supports it.

00:11:42.980 --> 00:11:45.260
And you don't get Python supports it unless someone sits down

00:11:45.340 --> 00:11:48.040
and actually does the hard work to make that happen,

00:11:48.220 --> 00:11:51.680
which is essentially what I was hired to, myself and Malcolm were hired to do.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:54.240
PyScript fits in a very similar boat.

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:59.600
You know, the web is undeniably a platform that is everywhere that you can't run Python in,

00:11:59.720 --> 00:12:02.360
or you couldn't run Python, or it was very hard to run Python in.

00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:08.520
And PyScript as an effort is essentially saying, okay, let's make it as straightforward as possible

00:12:08.620 --> 00:12:14.500
for me to just drop some Python into a browser and do web user interface stuff

00:12:15.100 --> 00:12:18.080
where instead of having to learn JavaScript and learn a whole new ecosystem,

00:12:18.120 --> 00:12:19.420
and learn a whole bunch of new set of tools.

00:12:19.560 --> 00:12:21.120
I can just use Python

00:12:22.319 --> 00:12:25.100
and open up that whole other ecosystem

00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:27.940
of places where you can run Python code

00:12:28.100 --> 00:12:30.120
as another place where you might want to do things.

00:12:30.820 --> 00:12:31.040
Yeah.

00:12:31.660 --> 00:12:32.560
And to give people a sense

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:33.700
of what's possible with PyScript,

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.880
it's very, very interesting.

00:12:38.419 --> 00:12:41.220
On iOS and also on Android,

00:12:41.320 --> 00:12:42.160
I'm sure I just haven't tried it,

00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:44.800
you can create progressive web apps

00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:46.780
and then say, save this to my home screen.

